         <h2>Latest Books Collection</h2>
         <ul class="lat">
             <li><b>Long Island Compromise:</b> "Long Island Compromise" delves into the intricacies of political negotiation and personal sacrifice as it chronicles the journey of Senator Jonathan Miller through the turbulent landscape of American governance. Set against the backdrop of a nation grappling with ideological divides and societal upheaval, the book explores Miller's pivotal role in brokering a landmark bipartisan agreement that reshapes healthcare policy. As Miller navigates through ethical dilemmas and personal challenges, author Sarah Townsend intricately weaves together themes of leadership, integrity, and the complexities of compromise in the pursuit of greater societal good. Through vivid storytelling and nuanced character development, "Long Island Compromise" offers readers a compelling narrative that transcends politics, resonating with themes of resilience, empathy, and the enduring quest for common ground in a divided world.<br>
             <a href="https://medium.com/@bridgetphira77/pdf-download-long-island-compromise-by-taffy-brodesser-akner-876be02e4fd1"><img src="island.jpg" height="350" width="233"><br>Get it now</a>
             </li><hr>
             <li><b>Driven: </b>"Driven" by Virat Kohli offers a compelling insight into the life and career of one of cricket's modern legends. Through this autobiography, Kohli takes readers on a journey from his early days of cricketing passion in Delhi to becoming the captain of the Indian national team. The book delves deep into his personal struggles, his relentless drive for excellence, and the pivotal moments that shaped his career. Kohli's candid narrative not only reveals his fierce determination on the field but also provides a glimpse into his thoughts on leadership, success, and the importance of mental toughness in sports. "Driven" is not just a story of cricketing achievements but also a testament to resilience and dedication, making it a must-read for fans of the sport and anyone inspired by tales of overcoming challenges to achieve greatness.<br><br>
